body:
@andrewhollomon not that I've changed the way this works as the original fix causes different problems (see #2336), so now to backup files with reparse points you'll have to use the `-L` flag.  This change will be in effect from v1.42 which I'm just about to release.

This will have the unfortunate effect that if you are using `rclone sync` with v1.42 and  you don't use `-L` then it will delete the files with reparse points from the backup, so please add the `-L` to your script before trying v1.42.  Also try first with --dry-run!

Thanks
